Today we headed to go see Santa & then to a parade for Blake’s dance. Welp, within 5 minutes of leaving, everyone was in a major mood, we got there & Santa wasn’t there because of the weather, we were all soaked from the rain & moods were even worse. 

We tried to figure the Santa thing out, but couldn’t. Then we were running late to Blake’s dance. I was stressing, she was stressing, it was pouring and it was all a giant mess. I felt so much pressure to do all the things when in reality we all needed to do NOTHING. So I said screw it, it wasn’t a competition. So I Texted Blake’s dance teacher, let her know we wouldn’t be there, we went to Red Robin and then came home and played games/watched movies. And guess what? We’re all in much better moods. 🫠 We can’t always cancel things but when we can, even if it makes us uncomfortable, it’s sometimes for the best to stop and reset. It’s only taken me 31 years to figure it out. 🤪

Even if it’s only an hour here and there at home. 🥹❤️ Someone once told me, one day your kids will all be grown up and it’ll just be you and your spouse. Don’t forget to keep that relationship alive too. It’s stuck with me because I think we get so wrapped up in life, we forget to prioritize things that are still important. Our kids are our world, but so is our relationship. 🖤

Okay - your newly crunchified girl Jess, over here making her own laundry detergent.😂 I did a LOT of research because some DIY laundry detergents aren’t great for your washer. So here’s what we came up with. I worked with a few recipes I found online so truly I can’t take full credit here. I just kind of combined some together & came up with this. Then tried it on a few loads & I’m impressed. Anyways - recipe: 
• 1 cup of epsom salt 
• 2 1/2 cups of washing soda
• 1/2 cup of sea salt 
• 3 1/2 cups of baking soda 
• 50 drops of essential oils (this is optional) - I like to drop 25 in, stir well & then 25 more in and stir well again.

Stir everything together REALLY well!

Use about 2 tablespoons per load! 🫶🏻🫶🏻 

#diy #laundrydetergent #simpleliving #cleanliving

Brain tumor - two words you don’t ever want to hear. Especially about your best friend, father of your babies and love of your life. Honestly it still feels like I’m living a dream even writing this. It doesn’t feel real. As most of you know, Marcus has been having pretty severe pain and neurological issues for about a year but it has really heightened since November. We’ve basically had to beg and beg for answers and help. Finally in December, we got him into a neurology clinic I had found online, but his appointment wasn’t until the end of March (two weeks ago). Well, the neurologist there ordered a full MRI work up, in fact it took 4 hours for the entire MRI from start to finish. Marcus was there on Thursday from 4-8pm. Flash forward to Saturday (yesterday) we were walking around the temple with the kids between conferences sessions (hence this pic) when his phone rang. I knew when he told me what the caller ID said that it wasn’t good news. They don’t call on a Saturday if it’s good news. I tried to listen intently next to his ear while the kids ran around us and Blake pushed baby’s stroller. Hearing the words “we found a reason for your symptoms - a brain lesion, a tumor.” I wrote down everything I could make out, names, phone numbers, everything. And here we are. A guess of three different options of what it could be, a 50/50 chance it’s cancerous or benign and next stop is meeting with the neurology oncologist. The doctor was amazing and truly a God send. He texted the oncologist for us, he’s gone above and beyond to ensure we get in quickly and answered all he could with the questions we asked. Truthfully, until about an hour ago, I’ve felt so defeated. So worn. I’ve wanted to scream. ANOTHER THING?! Are you kidding me?! How in the world are we supposed to pay for this? Get him the treatment he’s going to need? How are we going to tell our sweet babies? 😭 How am I going to Mom & take care of him while simultaneously trying to work? (Continued in comments)…..

Also @desertoakesgroup is the real MVP because he switched the light out for me too🥹❤️ Luckily for him it takes 10 min because for me it would’ve taken an hour of watching YouTube/doing it😂 

Okay so some tips: 
• baby wipe off any glue that seeps out the edges before it dries
• if you remove the mirror holders like I did make sure you glue the mirror to the wall or frame barely over it and nail gun into the wall if you have the space
• Let the construction adhesive dry the full 24 hours before removing the tape! (Or however long the specific one you get says on the bottle)

Total cost: truthfully I had everything minus the construction adhesive which was around $8. So if you have scraps jump on that😂 but if not, then it’ll most likely be around $30 depending on the size of mirror you have. So still really freaking affordable. And pro tip: just use paint you already have 🫶🏻

Real talk. For like a year now I’ve wondered what in the h I’m even doing here anymore. Why did I start this space almost 12 years ago? Why am I still here? What’s the point? And about a million other questions. This space is cluttered now, it’s not the same it used to be. Everyone is an “influencer” now and it’s majorly oversaturated if I’m being honest. My mom dying opened my eyes for a new life for us and new focuses which means I stepped back a little more in this space. But I also crave that creativity and I also still have to work a little bit. But like I said, it’s not the same. It’s not what it was and for a long time it felt heavy and forced and just “work”, a lot of work. Which lead to me being completely burnt out. Not only did we have the hardest two years of our lives but I was completely burnt out here too. So I lost a lot and that’s okay. But for awhile I’ve felt confused about my why, what, how and everything in between. 

But I had the realization today that well, originally I started this as my safe space if you will. My place to just be “me” and share whatever was on my heart. And somewhere along the way I lost that, I got pulled into the game of social media, into the “what I can and can’t do” and the “what I can and can’t posts” and well, honestly enough. I’m me and I just don’t have the mental capacity to care anymore. Our lives have changed so much, especially the last two years that welp, now you get the new, improved and growing Jess that is learning and trusting God everyday to align our lives with his. I’m not perfect, our lives are messy and most days I’m barely surviving. I don’t know what the future holds or even tomorrow, but welp I’m just rolling with life. I don’t have a “niche”, I try new things everyday and on this page you’re going to see just that. And well, all this rambling that probably doesn’t make sense to just say thanks for letting me be me 🫶🏻

Happy Father’s Day to our favorite guy🥹❤️ We are so freaking lucky to have you 🤟🏻 sorry this Father’s Day was lame & we spent the day driving 10.5 hours but thanks for being the best, most supportive, kindest, ever. I love you babe & I’m excited to see what our future holds. ❤️

Mom,

Honestly today was hard going to your resting place for the first time since your funeral. I’ve actually really dreaded it. There’s something weird about being at the place your physical body is and not being able to physically touch you or see you. Our Blake girl has been talking about how much she misses you all day since we got to idaho, but especially even more since going here today. She has told me about 10 times with tears in her eyes today “I just want to see her so badly Mommy, it’s not fair”. And truthfully, I don’t disagree. Since you’ve died our lives have been so hard. We’ve faced trials I never imagined we would, including your death too early and well, if I’ve ever needed my mom more, it’s been the last year and a half since you left this earth. And while there have been positives out of it all like we’ve grown closer together and closer to God than ever before, Which we needed….it just really has sucked without you❤️ But I’m hopeful (and trying to remain that way) for our future over the next couple of months…I know you’re helping things happen and fall into place for it all, even if it’s scary. 

Please hug me and my babies tight tonight. I know you love watching them, but you would have loved even more playing with them…and I wish I could have seen you with baby boy. He’s perfect mom, but you already know that, I know you guys knew each other before. Anyways…I miss you. More than words can explain, our relationship was complicated but I know you did your best and that you love me so much. I have a lot of peace in that. 

I know you’ve been reading this as I type it, there’s just something therapeutic about “putting it out there” in words. 

I love you. ❤️
Photo credit: Blake 🤟🏻🤍

Here’s some more claw clips tips for you 🤪🫶🏻 

• The more “claws” the better the hold 
• Double springs on the clip will also give you a better hold
• More Rounded “claws” will give you a better hold & doesn’t poke into your head as much 

But ultimately a good rule of thumb is, the longer the clip & claws/the more “claws” the better it’ll be for longer and thicker hair. But for us thinner girlies we can typically do either or❤️🫶🏻

Tips on wallpapering (because I’ve done it about 100 times now 😂)

• remove outlet covers first
• order more than you think you need length and width wise
• give yourself a little more at the top than you’d think
• don’t pull or stretch it as you go - if it doesn’t line up, pull it off and re-line it up. Stretching it will literally stretch the wallpaper and then it’ll never line up.
• a smoothing tool will be your bff - luckily Wallblush now sends you one!
• put a new blade on your box cutter before you start cutting and trimming 
• use the smoothing tool to follow the edges as you cut the excess off 
• air bubbles are some times inevitable - poke a tiny hole in it and then smooth it right out
• practice makes perfect 😘 this took me about 45 minutes, whereas the first time I did it, it took like 6 hours 🤪🫶🏻
